    <section id="postingbody">
        <div class="print-information print-qrcode-container">
            <p class="print-qrcode-label">QR Code Link to This Post</p>
            <div class="print-qrcode" data-location="http://billings.craigslist.org/fbh/6006354504.html"></div>
        </div>
Popeyes Louisianan Kitchen at Shiloh Crossing is seeking a high energy, customer oriented, responsible General Manager.  <br>
<br>
At Popeyes, you are more than an employee, you are an investment in success.   If you are friendly and enthusiastic and have a desire to be challenged . . . and appreciated. . . we're waiting to hear from you. Our Management team is dynamic and fun-loving with a passion for presenting a great dining experience to our customers and an enjoyable working environment for our team members.<br>
<br>
Great opportunities for career growth exist within this expanding Montana company.  Semi-monthly pay.  Potential starting salary of $40,000 with benefits depending upon Prior Experience and ATTITUDE. Raises and Bonuses available based upon Performance, Merit and ATTITUDE.<br>
<br>
********************************************************************************<br>
<br>
General Manager Job Description:<br>
•	Represents the restaurant to the customers and community.  <br>
•	Provides a high quality experience for all guests, increases guest engagement, and resolves guest complaints. <br>
•	Leads team with courtesy. Provides support and encouragement for team members.  <br>
•	Positions crew for shift. Coaches team members for successful shifts. Leads team to proper accomplishment of shift goals and position duties. Sets an example for all team members. <br>
•	Executes training programs for Managers and Crew. Achieves Brand Standards and follows Brand Procedures at all times. <br>
•	Efficiently manages labor costs and food waste. Correctly records inventory and places product orders using a budget. <br>
•	Is responsible for all cash within the restaurant, and proper accounting of deposits and payroll expenditures.<br>
•	Maintains precise record keeping<br>
•	Ensures the safety of the food and persons within the restaurant. <br>
•	Is responsible for personnel management tasks including recruiting, hiring, training, scheduling, evaluating, counseling, promoting, and firing.<br>
•	Coordinates repair and maintenance of store facilities and equipment.<br>
<br>
•	This position requires basic computer skills and willingness to submit to a background check.<br>
•	This job requires the abilities to: maintain equilibrium on slippery surfaces, reach items stored as high as 9ft, remain upright and moving constantly for a period of 5-10 hours, navigate narrow passageways shared with other people, open and close vacuum locking industrial machinery such as coolers and ovens, raise items from a lower to a higher position, move objects horizontally from position to position, type on a standard computer keyboard and operate a touch screen, grasp food items and operate tongs, communicate using the spoken word accurately, loudly, and quickly, perceive the nature of sounds at normal speaking level with or without correction, receive detailed information through oral communication, execute repetitive motion with the wrists, hands, and fingers, work at a counterspace 36" off the ground, respond to emergency situations. This job is classified as medium work: Exerting up to 50lbs of force occasionally, and up to 30lbs frequently to move objects a distance of 4ft-25ft. The manager is required to have visual acuity to operate fryers, CVAPs, chub warmers, and ovens, determine accuracy of orders, and food production, cleanliness of the dining room, restrooms, and kitchen, make general observation of facilities, equipment, food and employees, the Manager is subject to both indoor and outdoor conditions and to fumes such as smoke, fine dust such as flour in the air, and at times, poor ventilation.<br>
•	Preference will be given to applicants with post-secondary education. <br>
<br>
    </section>

